15/04/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Wrapping up a two-day visit to Syria, Turkish President Ahmet Necdet Sezer on Thursday (14 April) acknowledged Syria's willingness to withdraw its troops from Lebanon. 
"It was pleasing to see the political will of Syria to withdraw its solders from Lebanon be reaffirmed to us," Sezer told NTV. 
On a bilateral level, Sezer expressed satisfaction that relations with Syria had improved significantly over the past several years. 
(NTV - 14/04/05)
